1
00:00:08,216 --> 00:00:09,926
-<i>Euneo.</i>
-Yes<i>, euneo.</i>

2
00:00:11,094 --> 00:00:13,722
Oh, <i>euneo</i>. Sweetfish.

3
00:00:13,805 --> 00:00:14,639
Sweetfish.

4
00:00:14,723 --> 00:00:17,308
-Sweetfish. <i>Euneo</i>.
-<i>Euneo</i>.

5
00:00:17,392 --> 00:00:18,226
Yes, got it.

6
00:00:18,309 --> 00:00:20,228
He's a nice kid.

7
00:00:22,564 --> 00:00:23,940
You think so?

8
00:00:24,024 --> 00:00:26,276
Isn't that why you brought him here?

9
00:00:26,359 --> 00:00:29,821
I mean, he just showed up in Japan.

10
00:00:30,321 --> 00:00:32,032
Isn't that great?

11
00:00:33,283 --> 00:00:35,702
It feels livelier with him around.

12
00:00:36,828 --> 00:00:38,705
And your father looks so happy.

13
00:00:39,205 --> 00:00:40,915
They totally hit it off.

14
00:00:40,999 --> 00:00:41,833
Here.

15
00:00:44,461 --> 00:00:47,005
-Yeah, it's good.
-Good.

16
00:00:48,256 --> 00:00:53,178
He may not show it,
but your father was worried about you.

17
00:00:53,261 --> 00:00:54,554
He must be relieved.

18
00:00:57,307 --> 00:00:58,266
Sorry.

19
00:01:01,770 --> 00:01:06,566
It's a parent's job to worry,
even when there's nothing wrong.

20
00:01:13,031 --> 00:01:15,867
Hey. How's school?

21
00:01:16,785 --> 00:01:21,456
All you ever did was play ice hockey,
so you must have trouble studying.

22
00:01:21,539 --> 00:01:24,459
I'll graduate, at the very least.

23
00:01:24,542 --> 00:01:26,669
You don't have to push yourself.

24
00:01:27,420 --> 00:01:29,380
It's okay if you want to quit.

25
00:01:30,507 --> 00:01:31,925
More importantly,

26
00:01:33,051 --> 00:01:34,886
come visit us again.

27
00:01:37,055 --> 00:01:38,848
And bring Johan with you.

28
00:01:40,225 --> 00:01:43,478
But he's gonna serve in the military soon.

29
00:01:43,561 --> 00:01:44,646
What?

30
00:01:44,729 --> 00:01:47,190
Ryeowook is going soon too, you know.

31
00:01:47,273 --> 00:01:49,984
I was a pretty big fan of his.

32
00:01:50,068 --> 00:01:52,445
What? You listen to that stuff?

33
00:01:53,238 --> 00:01:56,324
I listen. I sing.

34
00:01:56,407 --> 00:01:57,992
I can dance too!

35
00:02:09,420 --> 00:02:10,630
Is it okay

36
00:02:12,132 --> 00:02:14,259
if I stay lost in Tokyo a bit longer?

37
00:02:17,929 --> 00:02:20,056
Stay lost to your heart's content.

38
00:02:26,229 --> 00:02:27,564
Hey, do you eat mushrooms?

39
00:02:27,647 --> 00:02:29,524
-Huh? What?
-Mushrooms.

40
00:02:29,607 --> 00:02:31,985
-Oh, I do.
-The <i>nimono </i>is ready too.

41
00:02:32,068 --> 00:02:33,820
Now, let's eat!

42
00:02:33,903 --> 00:02:36,447
Wait, you're already eating.

43
00:02:36,531 --> 00:02:37,407
All right.

44
00:02:37,490 --> 00:02:39,367
-Cheers!
-Cheers!

45
00:02:39,450 --> 00:02:42,078
<i>-Geonbae</i>!
-<i>Geonbae</i>!

46
00:02:44,372 --> 00:02:47,917
Eat some veggies. Here, go ahead.

47
00:02:55,884 --> 00:02:57,385
Hey, don't touch it.

48
00:02:58,720 --> 00:03:00,096
You'll get burned.

49
00:03:00,722 --> 00:03:02,223
-A flower!
-Don't play around!

50
00:03:02,307 --> 00:03:05,143
Draw a circle, then a flower!

51
00:03:08,980 --> 00:03:10,106
-Hey.
-Oh.

52
00:03:10,190 --> 00:03:11,232
You scared me.

53
00:03:17,113 --> 00:03:18,323
Should we join them?

54
00:03:21,492 --> 00:03:22,660
Wow!

55
00:03:23,870 --> 00:03:26,122
-Here, the bucket!
-Put it there.

56
00:03:30,126 --> 00:03:31,085
Whoa.

57
00:03:32,170 --> 00:03:34,881
Wow! The smoke!

58
00:03:34,964 --> 00:03:36,132
It's hot!

59
00:03:36,216 --> 00:03:38,009
Be careful! It's dangerous!

60
00:03:38,092 --> 00:03:39,302
Watch it!

61
00:03:45,183 --> 00:03:46,517
Want me to wash your back?

62
00:03:47,018 --> 00:03:47,936
Hmm?

63
00:03:48,019 --> 00:03:49,062
Your back.

64
00:03:50,855 --> 00:03:51,856
Okay.

65
00:03:53,566 --> 00:03:54,567
Here.

66
00:04:00,323 --> 00:04:05,495
Your uncle's paintings were really good.

67
00:04:06,746 --> 00:04:07,622
Yeah.

68
00:04:07,705 --> 00:04:11,668
I'll never forget your uncle's paintings

69
00:04:13,253 --> 00:04:15,004
or everything we did today.

70
00:04:16,464 --> 00:04:18,174
What are you talking about?

71
00:04:25,181 --> 00:04:26,516
Thank you.

72
00:04:32,480 --> 00:04:33,481
Sure.

73
00:04:38,486 --> 00:04:39,487
Yeah.

74
00:05:06,014 --> 00:05:07,557
Thank you very much.

75
00:05:08,308 --> 00:05:09,350
Come by again, okay?

76
00:05:09,434 --> 00:05:10,435
I will.

77
00:05:12,478 --> 00:05:13,521
<i>Abeoji</i>.

78
00:05:14,397 --> 00:05:15,440
<i>Eomeoni</i>.

79
00:05:21,195 --> 00:05:22,280
Bye, then.

80
00:05:22,363 --> 00:05:23,364
Okay.

81
00:05:25,700 --> 00:05:27,035
-Here.
-Oh.

82
00:05:27,702 --> 00:05:30,663
Let's go fishing next time.

83
00:05:31,831 --> 00:05:33,374
-Definitely.
-Yeah.

84
00:05:33,875 --> 00:05:35,335
Keep in touch.

85
00:05:36,461 --> 00:05:38,046
See you again!

86
00:05:38,129 --> 00:05:39,213
Now, now.

87
00:05:58,775 --> 00:06:00,234
-Take care, okay?
-Okay.

88
00:06:00,318 --> 00:06:01,861
-I'll keep in touch.
-Okay!

89
00:06:01,944 --> 00:06:03,821
Come by again!

90
00:06:03,905 --> 00:06:05,031
<i>Euneo!</i>

91
00:06:05,615 --> 00:06:06,866
Sweetfish!

92
00:06:21,172 --> 00:06:24,050
Next time, give me a heads-up
before you come visit, okay?

93
00:06:24,884 --> 00:06:25,927
Next time?

94
00:06:26,010 --> 00:06:27,011
Yeah.

95
00:06:29,263 --> 00:06:33,309
It's your turn to come visit me next time.

96
00:06:35,895 --> 00:06:37,563
-That's true.
-Yeah.

97
00:06:48,408 --> 00:06:49,409
What was that?

98
00:07:13,307 --> 00:07:14,892
Hmm?

99
00:07:15,476 --> 00:07:17,228
-You suck.
-What?

100
00:07:18,813 --> 00:07:20,481
It looks exactly like you.

101
00:07:21,899 --> 00:07:23,526
-Exactly like me?
-Yeah.

102
00:07:43,671 --> 00:07:49,051
TRAINING ELITE FORCES WHO FIGHT AND WIN

103
00:08:00,104 --> 00:08:00,980
Hello?

104
00:08:01,063 --> 00:08:03,774
<i>Hello? It's, uh…</i>

105
00:08:03,858 --> 00:08:04,859
Yeah?

106
00:08:05,693 --> 00:08:07,904
<i>Coach got a call.</i>

107
00:08:09,155 --> 00:08:10,323
<i>Arata is…</i>

108
00:08:23,252 --> 00:08:24,337
Come in.

109
00:08:45,399 --> 00:08:46,400
Hey.

110
00:09:05,253 --> 00:09:06,796
Why don't you sit?

111
00:09:06,879 --> 00:09:07,880
Okay.

112
00:09:28,734 --> 00:09:30,152
Long time no see.

113
00:09:31,195 --> 00:09:33,739
You're saying that now?

114
00:09:35,032 --> 00:09:36,117
True.

115
00:09:41,205 --> 00:09:43,040
You came by a lot, didn't you?

116
00:09:50,590 --> 00:09:51,674
Hey.

117
00:09:58,014 --> 00:09:59,432
About back then…

118
00:10:03,394 --> 00:10:04,270
I'm sorry.

119
00:10:04,353 --> 00:10:06,439
Whoa, stop.

120
00:10:07,898 --> 00:10:08,899
Wait.

121
00:10:10,901 --> 00:10:11,902
What?

122
00:10:15,323 --> 00:10:16,907
Are you here to apologize?

123
00:10:20,161 --> 00:10:21,162
I…

124
00:10:23,623 --> 00:10:24,832
When that happened…

125
00:10:29,337 --> 00:10:31,213
I couldn't protect you.

126
00:10:31,297 --> 00:10:33,049
I don't need that from you.

127
00:10:33,132 --> 00:10:36,344
I never thought you failed to protect me.

128
00:10:38,137 --> 00:10:39,513
It is what it is.

129
00:10:41,349 --> 00:10:44,560
I'll admit I didn't think
it would go around like that.

130
00:10:49,065 --> 00:10:50,775
But what could we do?

131
00:10:53,027 --> 00:10:55,446
You were simply protecting yourself.

132
00:10:59,283 --> 00:11:00,451
But that's why--

133
00:11:00,534 --> 00:11:03,412
I was prepared for that.

134
00:11:07,917 --> 00:11:10,086
I was fully aware of what might happen…

135
00:11:14,173 --> 00:11:16,092
when I confessed my feelings to you.

136
00:11:19,762 --> 00:11:21,972
I wanted you to know

137
00:11:23,891 --> 00:11:24,975
how I felt.

138
00:11:28,938 --> 00:11:33,984
<i>If, right now</i>

139
00:11:34,985 --> 00:11:41,534
<i>I can be true to my feelings</i>

140
00:11:55,214 --> 00:11:56,090
Are you ready?

141
00:11:56,173 --> 00:11:57,591
-Yeah.
-Okay.

142
00:12:00,010 --> 00:12:02,096
I'm sorry it's heavy.

143
00:12:02,179 --> 00:12:03,180
It's fine.

144
00:12:05,933 --> 00:12:07,143
Go on ahead.

145
00:12:07,226 --> 00:12:08,310
Sure.

146
00:12:10,938 --> 00:12:11,897
Thanks.

147
00:12:11,981 --> 00:12:12,982
No worries.

148
00:12:51,979 --> 00:12:57,359
<i>My admiration</i>

149
00:12:57,443 --> 00:13:02,573
<i>And my love</i>

150
00:13:03,991 --> 00:13:08,496
<i>Will fly to the wide open sky</i>

151
00:13:09,288 --> 00:13:15,836
<i>And shine brightly</i>

152
00:13:16,837 --> 00:13:22,176
<i>I believe in future</i>

153
00:13:23,135 --> 00:13:27,306
<i>I believe</i>

154
00:13:33,437 --> 00:13:35,231
All firing lines, firing complete!

155
00:13:47,576 --> 00:13:48,577
Keep a straight line!

156
00:13:48,661 --> 00:13:50,913
Keep a straight line!

157
00:13:54,458 --> 00:13:55,459
Johan.

158
00:13:57,086 --> 00:13:58,754
Give these a proper polish.

159
00:13:58,838 --> 00:14:00,464
Polish mine too.

160
00:14:00,548 --> 00:14:02,216
Do mine too.

161
00:14:03,467 --> 00:14:05,761
Being an ex-boxer goes to your head, huh?

162
00:14:05,845 --> 00:14:08,138
Don't get cocky.

163
00:14:09,390 --> 00:14:10,724
Troops, halt!

164
00:14:20,150 --> 00:14:22,570
Time's moving so slow.

165
00:14:23,237 --> 00:14:24,655
And you call this food?

166
00:14:27,908 --> 00:14:29,994
My youth is like a piece of shit.

167
00:14:35,332 --> 00:14:38,752
At times like these…

168
00:14:41,005 --> 00:14:43,424
think about the fun times you've had.

169
00:14:46,302 --> 00:14:47,845
The fun times?

170
00:14:48,762 --> 00:14:49,763
Yeah.

171
00:14:50,472 --> 00:14:53,726
Or about the fun times
that are bound to come.

172
00:14:59,023 --> 00:15:00,149
Welcome.

173
00:15:04,778 --> 00:15:06,196
-Yo.
-Hey.

174
00:15:08,616 --> 00:15:10,326
How was the interview?

175
00:15:10,409 --> 00:15:12,953
Man, it was a total bust.

176
00:15:13,037 --> 00:15:14,914
It felt like it went nowhere.

177
00:15:14,997 --> 00:15:17,708
-Please put your bags in here.
-Thank you.

178
00:15:18,417 --> 00:15:20,336
-Anyway, good work.
-Thanks.

179
00:15:21,253 --> 00:15:23,297
You're so lucky.

180
00:15:23,380 --> 00:15:25,633
You already landed a job
through connections.

181
00:15:25,716 --> 00:15:26,842
I guess so.

182
00:15:27,343 --> 00:15:31,180
Still, it kind of sucks
not getting to choose for myself.

183
00:15:31,263 --> 00:15:33,182
I feel a bit conflicted about it.

184
00:15:33,265 --> 00:15:35,434
My job was decided automatically.

185
00:15:35,517 --> 00:15:37,353
That's what makes me jealous.

186
00:15:38,103 --> 00:15:39,355
What about your hometown?

187
00:15:39,438 --> 00:15:41,440
You could take over your dad's business.

188
00:15:41,523 --> 00:15:43,776
No, I don't think that's happening.

189
00:15:43,859 --> 00:15:45,569
I see.

190
00:15:46,195 --> 00:15:47,947
-Some beer?
-Yeah.

191
00:15:48,948 --> 00:15:50,699
Thanks.

192
00:15:53,077 --> 00:15:54,161
All right.

193
00:15:54,244 --> 00:15:55,829
Let's drink.

194
00:15:55,913 --> 00:15:56,830
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

195
00:16:02,711 --> 00:16:03,629
That's good.

196
00:16:03,712 --> 00:16:05,547
-That hits the spot.
-Yeah.

197
00:16:07,383 --> 00:16:09,969
What should we eat today?

198
00:16:10,552 --> 00:16:12,304
I'm definitely getting the tongue.

199
00:16:15,599 --> 00:16:16,558
Hello?

200
00:16:16,642 --> 00:16:19,061
-<i>Hello? Ryu?</i>
-Yeah.

201
00:16:19,144 --> 00:16:22,439
<i>Hey, I think I'm close by now, but…</i>

202
00:16:22,523 --> 00:16:25,192
Yeah? Okay, got it.

203
00:16:25,275 --> 00:16:27,194
I'll come outside then.

204
00:16:27,736 --> 00:16:28,779
-<i>Thanks.</i>
-Sure.

205
00:16:28,862 --> 00:16:29,989
<i>I think I'm here!</i>

206
00:16:30,072 --> 00:16:31,532
-Oh, Ryu!
-Hey!

207
00:16:31,615 --> 00:16:34,243
-You found it?
-Yeah, just barely.

208
00:16:34,326 --> 00:16:35,619
-I'll take that.
-Thanks.

209
00:16:35,703 --> 00:16:38,414
-Of course.
-I'm so glad I made it.

210
00:16:40,040 --> 00:16:42,292
-Good evening.
-Good evening. I'll take these.

211
00:16:42,376 --> 00:16:45,295
-Thank you. Sorry for the trouble.
-Thank you.

212
00:16:45,379 --> 00:16:47,297
I'm sorry I'm late.

213
00:16:47,381 --> 00:16:49,258
This is Sumiko, who I told you about.

214
00:16:49,758 --> 00:16:51,927
H-Hello! I'm Super Scrappy Seiichi!

215
00:16:53,721 --> 00:16:54,555
"Super Scrappy"?

216
00:16:54,638 --> 00:16:56,432
We played ice hockey together. He's Sei--

217
00:16:56,515 --> 00:16:58,100
Seiichi.

218
00:16:59,393 --> 00:17:01,520
-Nice to meet you.
-Nice to meet you too.

219
00:17:02,229 --> 00:17:03,814
-Please have a seat.
-Okay.

220
00:17:03,897 --> 00:17:05,107
What's with this guy?

221
00:17:05,190 --> 00:17:08,986
It's amazing that you went abroad
right out of high school.

222
00:17:09,069 --> 00:17:11,196
It's like, you take initiative.

223
00:17:11,280 --> 00:17:13,323
Anyway, it's really cool.

224
00:17:15,617 --> 00:17:20,164
My parents are divorced,
and my family situation is complicated.

225
00:17:20,247 --> 00:17:23,292
I'm pretty much estranged from my mother,

226
00:17:23,375 --> 00:17:26,253
so part of me was like,
"I need a job quick!"

227
00:17:27,004 --> 00:17:31,592
So, I secretly borrowed money
from my dad, who lives separately.

228
00:17:32,092 --> 00:17:34,928
That makes you even cooler.

229
00:17:35,429 --> 00:17:38,140
All we had was ice hockey, huh?

230
00:17:38,223 --> 00:17:40,267
You have your parents' connections too.

231
00:17:40,350 --> 00:17:41,685
Shut up.

232
00:17:41,769 --> 00:17:44,229
Here, Sumiko. Eat this.

233
00:17:44,313 --> 00:17:45,939
Thank you.

234
00:17:46,774 --> 00:17:48,108
So good!

235
00:17:49,693 --> 00:17:51,445
-Oh, hey.
-Yeah?

236
00:17:51,528 --> 00:17:55,657
Do you have
hair conditioner at your place?

237
00:17:57,034 --> 00:17:57,868
Nope.

238
00:17:57,951 --> 00:18:01,413
Right? I'm so glad I asked.
I'll get some on the way back.

239
00:18:01,497 --> 00:18:03,665
I'm a guy living alone, so…

240
00:18:03,749 --> 00:18:05,751
-Um…
-I might be missing some stuff.

241
00:18:05,834 --> 00:18:07,211
May I?

242
00:18:07,294 --> 00:18:08,378
Hmm?

243
00:18:08,462 --> 00:18:10,547
So, um…

244
00:18:11,048 --> 00:18:14,635
Are you staying at Ryu's place, Sumiko?

245
00:18:14,718 --> 00:18:16,220
Yeah, I am.

246
00:18:16,303 --> 00:18:20,015
That's where I'm staying for now
until I find my own place in Tokyo.

247
00:18:20,099 --> 00:18:21,100
What?

248
00:18:22,101 --> 00:18:23,602
What? Uh…

249
00:18:24,103 --> 00:18:27,523
Hmm, but is that really okay?

250
00:18:28,065 --> 00:18:29,900
There's nothing going on between us.

251
00:18:29,983 --> 00:18:30,984
Yeah.

252
00:18:31,068 --> 00:18:33,320
But…

253
00:18:33,403 --> 00:18:34,404
I know!

254
00:18:34,988 --> 00:18:38,158
Maybe I'll stay over at your place too.

255
00:18:38,242 --> 00:18:39,284
What?!

256
00:18:39,368 --> 00:18:40,410
We're here.

257
00:18:40,494 --> 00:18:41,703
Which floor, Ryu?

258
00:18:41,787 --> 00:18:42,996
-Second floor.
-Second?

259
00:18:43,080 --> 00:18:43,914
That's fine.

260
00:18:43,997 --> 00:18:45,541
I'm okay. Go ahead.

261
00:18:46,041 --> 00:18:48,168
-Can you make it?
-I'm fine. I work out.

262
00:18:48,252 --> 00:18:49,586
-You're sweating!
-I'm not.

263
00:18:49,670 --> 00:18:51,171
You work out?

264
00:18:51,255 --> 00:18:54,633
There we go! I'm fine. Leave it to me.

265
00:18:54,716 --> 00:18:55,884
You can do it, Seiichi!

266
00:18:55,968 --> 00:18:57,136
I told you, I'm fine.

267
00:18:57,219 --> 00:18:58,804
-All right.
-Here, Sumiko.

268
00:18:58,887 --> 00:19:00,889
-Oh, thanks.
-I'll bring this inside.

269
00:19:00,973 --> 00:19:01,974
Are you good?

270
00:19:02,057 --> 00:19:03,475
Phew.

271
00:19:06,145 --> 00:19:08,063
Whoa.

272
00:19:08,772 --> 00:19:10,524
You're really living alone!

273
00:19:10,607 --> 00:19:11,567
I sure am.

274
00:19:11,650 --> 00:19:13,193
You keep it pretty clean.

275
00:19:13,277 --> 00:19:14,278
Yeah, I guess.

276
00:19:19,992 --> 00:19:22,619
Wait, are you interested in caregiving?

277
00:19:22,703 --> 00:19:25,831
Not seriously or anything. Just a little.

278
00:19:26,415 --> 00:19:27,249
I'll take these.

279
00:19:27,332 --> 00:19:30,252
-Thanks.
-Man, I could never handle it.

280
00:19:31,086 --> 00:19:33,755
What you can't handle
is that strict caregiver.

281
00:19:33,839 --> 00:19:35,090
Shut up.

282
00:19:35,757 --> 00:19:37,634
-Oh! Sumiko.
-Hm?

283
00:19:37,718 --> 00:19:38,844
Sit here.

284
00:19:38,927 --> 00:19:40,053
-Okay.
-Yeah.

285
00:19:40,137 --> 00:19:42,639
-Come. Over here.
-Thank you.

286
00:19:44,349 --> 00:19:45,350
-UNO!
-What?

287
00:19:45,434 --> 00:19:47,895
-Wait a minute. Oh, no.
-This is bad!

288
00:19:47,978 --> 00:19:48,812
Hold on.

289
00:19:48,896 --> 00:19:51,899
-Please let me win!
-Wait, what should I do?

290
00:19:51,982 --> 00:19:53,817
-Come on!
-Here. I'll play this.

291
00:19:53,901 --> 00:19:54,943
What?

292
00:19:55,027 --> 00:19:57,279
-Come on!
-I don't have any. Oh, this one.

293
00:19:57,362 --> 00:19:59,072
I'm gonna take this call.

294
00:19:59,156 --> 00:20:00,240
Huh?

295
00:20:00,324 --> 00:20:03,160
Wait. You can't run away
because you're about to lose.

296
00:20:03,243 --> 00:20:04,745
That's not what I'm doing.

297
00:20:05,454 --> 00:20:06,788
You guys keep playing.

298
00:20:13,170 --> 00:20:14,504
Hello?

299
00:20:15,005 --> 00:20:16,965
<i>Did Sumiko arrive?</i>

300
00:20:17,049 --> 00:20:18,050
Yeah.

301
00:20:18,842 --> 00:20:20,928
We were playing UNO just now.

302
00:20:21,553 --> 00:20:23,889
<i>Huh? "Uno"?</i>

303
00:20:24,473 --> 00:20:25,474
UNO.

304
00:20:26,058 --> 00:20:27,726
Wait, don't you have UNO in Korea?

305
00:20:29,353 --> 00:20:30,354
"Uno."

306
00:20:31,063 --> 00:20:32,898
Oh, sweetfish.

307
00:20:35,067 --> 00:20:36,860
<i>No, not that.</i>

308
00:20:36,944 --> 00:20:38,654
<i>Um, how do I put this?</i>

309
00:20:39,154 --> 00:20:41,031
<i>It's the name of a card game.</i>

310
00:20:41,990 --> 00:20:43,200
Oh.

311
00:20:45,619 --> 00:20:46,662
Damn.

312
00:20:47,371 --> 00:20:50,415
Now I want to eat <i>Abeoji</i>'s <i>euneo</i>.

313
00:20:51,458 --> 00:20:52,918
I'll let him know.

314
00:20:53,877 --> 00:20:55,671
<i>I want to eat it right now.</i>

315
00:20:57,005 --> 00:20:58,006
Yeah.

316
00:20:58,674 --> 00:21:00,509
After my military service ends,

317
00:21:02,219 --> 00:21:07,891
I've decided to become a coach
at my coach's gym for now.

318
00:21:08,892 --> 00:21:10,394
<i>Oh, I see.</i>

319
00:21:12,271 --> 00:21:13,772
That's good.

320
00:21:14,564 --> 00:21:16,775
<i>Yeah, I'm relieved.</i>

321
00:21:18,360 --> 00:21:19,569
Good luck.

322
00:21:20,946 --> 00:21:22,614
<i>Tell me if I'm wrong.</i>

323
00:21:23,282 --> 00:21:27,953
Are you and Ryu, by any chance…

324
00:21:29,621 --> 00:21:31,581
Of course not.

325
00:21:34,584 --> 00:21:35,794
Is that so?

326
00:21:36,378 --> 00:21:38,797
Well, that makes sense.

327
00:21:39,589 --> 00:21:40,590
Sorry about that.

328
00:21:40,674 --> 00:21:44,052
No, there's no need to apologize.

329
00:21:45,095 --> 00:21:46,221
Sorry.

330
00:21:47,472 --> 00:21:48,682
What about you?

331
00:21:48,765 --> 00:21:50,517
Is there anyone you like?

332
00:21:51,143 --> 00:21:53,729
Huh? Oh.

333
00:21:53,812 --> 00:21:55,564
Hmm…

334
00:21:56,523 --> 00:22:00,944
No, I don't… Well, maybe I do.

335
00:22:01,028 --> 00:22:02,988
What?

336
00:22:03,071 --> 00:22:04,614
What was that?

337
00:22:04,698 --> 00:22:06,616
Who is it? Someone from school?

338
00:22:06,700 --> 00:22:07,951
Are you guys going out?

339
00:22:08,035 --> 00:22:10,912
Oh, no. We're not.

340
00:22:10,996 --> 00:22:12,414
-Oh?
-Yeah.

341
00:22:12,497 --> 00:22:14,541
I don't have a girlfriend.

342
00:22:14,624 --> 00:22:18,170
I see. What does she do?

343
00:22:18,670 --> 00:22:20,297
Um…

344
00:22:24,051 --> 00:22:27,387
She might be drinking.

345
00:22:27,471 --> 00:22:29,931
Oh? So, she likes to drink.

346
00:22:33,185 --> 00:22:37,564
And she might be eating potato chips.

347
00:22:41,318 --> 00:22:42,319
Huh?

348
00:22:44,738 --> 00:22:45,739
Huh?

349
00:22:51,787 --> 00:22:55,332
A love at first sight… kind of thing.

350
00:22:57,542 --> 00:22:58,960
Oh…

351
00:23:00,462 --> 00:23:01,630
Um…

352
00:23:04,383 --> 00:23:07,969
Let's start off as friends… kind of thing.

353
00:23:09,054 --> 00:23:10,222
Right.

354
00:23:10,847 --> 00:23:17,854
Like, we take it step by step,
then you make a final call kind of thing?

355
00:23:23,026 --> 00:23:24,528
Whoa!

356
00:23:25,028 --> 00:23:28,657
-What are you doing, Ryu?
-Hey. Come on!

357
00:23:28,740 --> 00:23:29,991
What the hell?

358
00:23:30,075 --> 00:23:32,035
-You're so freaked out.
-That scared me.

359
00:23:32,119 --> 00:23:34,371
What is it, huh?

360
00:23:34,454 --> 00:23:36,832
Come on, stop messing with me!

361
00:23:36,915 --> 00:23:38,333
What were you talking about?

362
00:23:38,417 --> 00:23:40,627
Nothing.

363
00:23:40,710 --> 00:23:42,879
-Jeez. Come on.
-Yeah?

364
00:23:42,963 --> 00:23:44,506
Let's play UNO.

365
00:23:44,589 --> 00:23:46,716
Huh? You guys weren't playing?

366
00:23:46,800 --> 00:23:48,427
Well, you ran away.

367
00:23:57,394 --> 00:23:58,603
Attention!

368
00:23:59,521 --> 00:24:01,231
Salute your superiors!

369
00:24:01,314 --> 00:24:02,774
Loyalty!

370
00:24:02,858 --> 00:24:03,859
Loyalty!

371
00:24:04,359 --> 00:24:06,278
Take care! We're going now.

372
00:24:06,361 --> 00:24:07,529
Thank you for your service.

373
00:24:11,783 --> 00:24:13,118
Dad!

374
00:24:15,787 --> 00:24:18,039
How have you been?

375
00:24:52,824 --> 00:24:54,659
Good work.

376
00:24:56,328 --> 00:24:58,413
I bet you're super buff now, huh?

377
00:24:58,914 --> 00:25:00,916
<i>I was already buff.</i>

378
00:25:03,335 --> 00:25:05,003
<i>It's finally over.</i>

379
00:25:05,086 --> 00:25:06,379
Yeah.

380
00:25:07,047 --> 00:25:08,256
I'm glad.

381
00:25:09,132 --> 00:25:11,343
<i>Yeah. I'm glad too.</i>

382
00:25:11,843 --> 00:25:14,387
Anyway, I've got my plane ticket
for next week.

383
00:25:15,055 --> 00:25:17,432
<i>You better clean your house properly.</i>

384
00:25:17,516 --> 00:25:18,517
Okay.

385
00:25:22,145 --> 00:25:23,730
<i>I got paged. I'm gonna go.</i>

386
00:25:23,813 --> 00:25:25,106
<i>I'll call you again.</i>

387
00:25:25,190 --> 00:25:26,775
Oh, okay. Bye.

388
00:25:26,858 --> 00:25:28,235
<i>Yep. Annyeong.</i>

389
00:25:53,927 --> 00:25:55,345
We're not open yet--

390
00:25:55,428 --> 00:25:56,263
Ta-da!

391
00:25:56,346 --> 00:25:59,808
Oh! You're alive?

392
00:26:00,433 --> 00:26:03,061
Don't kill me off like that.

393
00:26:03,144 --> 00:26:04,312
I'm just kidding.

394
00:26:04,813 --> 00:26:06,439
Hold on a second.

395
00:26:08,316 --> 00:26:10,694
I've been saving something for you.

396
00:26:10,777 --> 00:26:12,445
What is it?

397
00:26:12,529 --> 00:26:13,738
Just wait.

398
00:26:17,075 --> 00:26:18,577
Ta-da!

399
00:26:18,660 --> 00:26:20,203
Isn't that expensive?

400
00:26:20,287 --> 00:26:21,788
It is.

401
00:26:25,375 --> 00:26:26,876
Welcome back from prison.

402
00:26:26,960 --> 00:26:28,712
I was discharged from the military.

403
00:26:36,511 --> 00:26:37,762
What about the soda?

404
00:26:37,846 --> 00:26:39,764
You drink expensive liquor neat.

405
00:26:41,016 --> 00:26:42,017
Cheers.

406
00:26:42,892 --> 00:26:43,893
Cheers.

407
00:27:19,596 --> 00:27:21,348
Hey, Hyeong.

408
00:27:21,431 --> 00:27:23,433
Wow, this place is great.

409
00:27:23,516 --> 00:27:25,602
Sorry, we're not open yet.

410
00:27:25,685 --> 00:27:29,856
What? That guy's a customer. Are we not?

411
00:27:29,939 --> 00:27:32,025
Hey, sit.

412
00:27:32,108 --> 00:27:34,152
Are you discriminating against us?

413
00:27:36,404 --> 00:27:37,572
I'll be right with you.

414
00:27:37,656 --> 00:27:40,659
Don't they even have a menu?

415
00:27:40,742 --> 00:27:42,410
Here's the menu.

416
00:27:43,161 --> 00:27:45,705
Hey, I heard you're gay.

417
00:27:47,624 --> 00:27:49,292
I knew it, see?

418
00:27:49,376 --> 00:27:51,503
That's a soft ass!

419
00:27:56,299 --> 00:27:57,258
Are you gay too?

420
00:27:59,386 --> 00:28:02,597
Little gay, are you mad?

421
00:28:03,181 --> 00:28:05,475
No, I'm sorry, sir.

422
00:28:05,558 --> 00:28:07,852
Sir, I'm sorry.

423
00:28:07,936 --> 00:28:11,106
I'm sorry.

424
00:28:11,189 --> 00:28:13,233
Read the room!

425
00:28:17,904 --> 00:28:19,406
Johan, don't hit him!

426
00:28:19,489 --> 00:28:20,323
Go ahead. Hit me!

427
00:28:20,407 --> 00:28:22,784
Hit him, you bastard.

428
00:28:36,214 --> 00:28:38,675
You're seriously done for.

429
00:29:51,331 --> 00:29:52,665
"Former pro boxer

430
00:29:52,749 --> 00:29:58,338
causes violent incident at a gay bar
right after military discharge."

431
00:29:59,047 --> 00:30:01,132
Now that's a sensational headline, huh?

432
00:30:01,216 --> 00:30:02,801
Mr. Shim.

433
00:30:04,093 --> 00:30:06,137
Why are you here?

434
00:30:06,721 --> 00:30:09,015
I came to destroy your life.

435
00:30:12,477 --> 00:30:13,311
What?

436
00:30:16,397 --> 00:30:17,398
You leaked it.

437
00:30:19,859 --> 00:30:20,693
What?

438
00:30:20,777 --> 00:30:22,654
You leaked that stuff about me,
didn't you?!

439
00:30:23,446 --> 00:30:26,115
What are you talking about?

440
00:30:31,996 --> 00:30:33,748
Here! Over here!

441
00:30:34,249 --> 00:30:35,667
Right here.

442
00:30:36,960 --> 00:30:38,586
It's that guy in white.

443
00:30:39,295 --> 00:30:40,296
That one.

444
00:30:41,005 --> 00:30:43,258
No. No!

445
00:30:43,758 --> 00:30:45,009
It's not me. Mr. Shim.

446
00:30:45,093 --> 00:30:46,761
I'm not the one who leaked it!

447
00:30:48,471 --> 00:30:50,557
Mr. Shim! It wasn't me.

448
00:30:50,640 --> 00:30:52,976
It's not me!

449
00:30:53,059 --> 00:30:56,062
Wait, please. Mr. Shim!

450
00:33:07,652 --> 00:33:10,571
Subtitle translation by: Remi Miura
